CAPE TOWN – Public Enterprises Minister Pravin Gordhan on Monday announced the appointment of an interim board for South Africa's cash-strapped state-owned arms manufacturer, Denel. Monhla Hlala, former chairwoman of the Airports Company of South Africa, has been appointed board chair, according to a statement from the ministry. WATCH: #Denel’s interim board Chairperson Monhla Hlala addresses media. Says the new board will focus on finalising the entity’s 2017/18 financial statements. pic.twitter.com/HMUXktWNV3 READ: Calls for Denel to come clean on its finances The rest of the interim board are Zoli Kunene, Tshilidzi Marwala, General TT Matanzima, Gloria Serobe, Talib Sadiq, Sue Rabkin, Sibusiso Sibisi, Cheryl Carolus, Nonzukiso Siyotula, Thami Magazi, and Martin Mnisi. #GuptaLeaks: How the Guptas screwed Denel Denel is the latest in a string of state-owned enterprise to undergo a shake-up due to governance and liquidity issues. WATCH: New #Denel interim Chairperson Monhla Hlala speaks on the board’s appointment. The board was announced by Public Enterprises Minister Pravin #Gordhan pic.twitter.com/f2qqSRWrhb African News Agency